name: cred-rea-fish-team-stationary-point-count-surveys-at-howland-pacific-remote-island-areas-p-2006
notes: Stationary Point Counts at 4 stations at each survey site were surveyed as part of Rapid Ecological Assessments (REA) conducted at 6 sites around Howland in the Pacific Remote Island Areas (PRIAs) during 15 January - 6 February 2006 in the NOAA Hi'ialakai (HI0601) Reef Assessment and Monitoring Program (RAMP) Cruise. Raw survey data included species level abundance estimates.
